section.section:
A notice under this subsection shall include:
The name and address of the party seeking to create the lien;
A statement of intent to create a lien;
An identification of the ground lease;
A statement that the ground lease is registered with the State Department of Assessments and Taxation;
The amount of ground rent alleged to be due;
A description of the property sufficient to identify the property;
A statement that the party to whom notice is given under this subsection has the right to object to the establishment of a lien by filing a complaint in the circuit court and the right to a hearing;
An explanation of the procedure to file a complaint and request a hearing; and
A statement that, unless the past due ground rent is paid or a complaint is filed under subsection (f) of this section within 45 days after the notice is served, a lien will be imposed on the property.
